Conviction?
He's liable to be your next victim.

488
00:55:32,537 --> 00:55:34,789
What are you asking for, lieutenant?

489
00:55:34,956 --> 00:55:40,086
I'm not asking you to follow him, inspector.
For the last goddamn time, I'm telling you.

490
00:55:40,253 --> 00:55:41,421
Next.

491
00:55:43,006 --> 00:55:47,469
Nick Royale, Palancio's number-one hitter.

492
00:55:47,635 --> 00:55:49,554
He's had good training.

493
00:56:13,870 --> 00:56:15,163
What's happening?

494
00:56:15,330 --> 00:56:18,500
Nothing, just a lot of peeping and checking,
checking and peeping.

495
00:56:18,666 --> 00:56:21,795
I knew an old boy once
who used to keep pigs under his bed.

496
00:56:21,961 --> 00:56:23,671
Pigs? The eating kind?

497
00:56:23,838 --> 00:56:28,009
The eating kind.
Is all you ever think of your stomach?

498
00:56:33,807 --> 00:56:36,476
That's very interesting,
but I think we better get going.

499
00:56:36,643 --> 00:56:37,936
Yeah.

500
00:58:00,018 --> 00:58:03,688
- They're splitting up. Which one, Harry?
- We'll stay with these two.

501
00:58:05,398 --> 00:58:08,067
Across the bridge,
it's out of our jurisdiction.

502
00:58:08,234 --> 00:58:09,486
Yeah.

503
00:58:13,573 --> 00:58:14,741
Well?

504
00:58:15,575 --> 00:58:16,868
Stick with the money.

505
00:58:39,599 --> 00:58:41,059
Pull over and stop.

506
00:58:56,616 --> 00:59:00,161
What are you trying to do?
He doesn't even know we're cops.

507
00:59:00,954 --> 00:59:04,791
He may panic, and besides,
we don't belong over here anyway.

508
00:59:04,958 --> 00:59:06,543
I hope he does panic.

509
00:59:08,503 --> 00:59:10,964
Then I'll get him for 23 other murders.

510
00:59:11,130 --> 00:59:13,299
And if he doesn't...

511
00:59:13,466 --> 00:59:16,636
...then I may be right about something
that's been nagging at me.

512
00:59:16,803 --> 00:59:18,805
I sure hope I'm not.

513
00:59:19,305 --> 00:59:20,682
What?

514
00:59:20,848 --> 00:59:23,309
I don't wanna be winning bets
for anybody.

515
00:59:37,031 --> 00:59:39,325
Go a little faster, I'm on their side.

516
00:59:40,159 --> 00:59:42,912
- Roll down your window.
- What? Are you out of your mind?

517
00:59:43,079 --> 00:59:46,332
- I've never been wrong yet, have I?
- I don't know why I'm doing this.

518
00:59:46,499 --> 00:59:50,503
- Say, excuse me. Could you help us out?
- What do you want?

519
00:59:50,712 --> 00:59:53,089
Maybe you could help us,
we seem to be lost.

520
00:59:53,256 --> 00:59:56,718
We were looking for the entrance
to San Quentin. You know where that is?

521
00:59:56,884 --> 00:59:58,928
It's back there. Don't you see too good?

522
00:59:59,095 --> 01:00:03,099
Yeah, I see fine. I just wanted to know
whether you knew where San Quentin was.

523
01:00:03,349 --> 01:00:06,227
And you do, don't you, asshole?

524
01:00:13,026 --> 01:00:15,528
Get you yet, you son of a bitch.

525
01:00:19,240 --> 01:00:22,035
You always gotta do things your way,
don't you?

526
01:00:22,201 --> 01:00:24,537
No wonder Briggs stays on your tail.

527
01:00:26,539 --> 01:00:31,044
You do things someone else's way
and you take your life in your own hands.

528
01:00:50,897 --> 01:00:53,232
That son of a bitch Guzman.

529
01:00:54,067 --> 01:00:57,362
He hasn't gone out for almost
24 hours now.

530
01:01:23,429 --> 01:01:25,223
Hey, one of our guys took a spill.

531
01:01:26,683 --> 01:01:30,520
It's Charlie McCoy. Seems to be okay.

532
01:01:30,687 --> 01:01:32,438
Let me take a look.

533
01:01:33,523 --> 01:01:35,566
Yeah, he's okay.

534
01:01:45,993 --> 01:01:47,662
There he is.

535
01:01:48,621 --> 01:01:52,667
So all you've got to do
is sit around all day, Guzman?

536
01:02:24,323 --> 01:02:26,325
This coke is out of sight.

537
01:02:26,492 --> 01:02:28,953
Oh, Guzman is the man, baby.

538
01:02:29,996 --> 01:02:32,206
Oh, you bitch. Don't spill it.

539
01:02:32,665 --> 01:02:34,959
That stuff's worth $900 an ounce.

540
01:02:35,334 --> 01:02:36,836
You better not spill it.

541
01:02:37,962 --> 01:02:39,839
Don't get so uptight.

542
01:02:40,006 --> 01:02:44,135
Nobody says "don't" to me.
You understand? Nobody.

543
01:02:46,554 --> 01:02:48,347
I never touch the stuff.

544
01:02:48,848 --> 01:02:51,058
You wanna put that over there now?

545
01:03:16,375 --> 01:03:18,795
Take over for me, will you, Ed?

546
01:03:45,822 --> 01:03:48,115
Damn, I wish something would happen.

547
01:03:48,282 --> 01:03:49,784
Take it easy.

548
01:03:49,951 --> 01:03:53,246
That's what stakeouts are all about.
Waiting.

549
01:05:07,945 --> 01:05:10,114
It's a cop. Oh, no!

550
01:05:10,281 --> 01:05:13,159
No! No! No, please! No!

551
01:05:19,498 --> 01:05:21,459
Frank!

552
01:06:30,277 --> 01:06:33,322
- Just what the hell is going on?
- Somebody killed a cop.

553
01:06:33,489 --> 01:06:36,450
Folks, there's been a little trouble here.
Everyone stand back.

554
01:06:36,617 --> 01:06:38,494
Please, ma'am, move back.

555
01:06:41,414 --> 01:06:43,290
There's been some trouble.

556
01:06:44,583 --> 01:06:45,626
What happened?

557
01:06:47,086 --> 01:06:49,088
Everything seems to be all right, folks.

558
01:06:49,255 --> 01:06:51,132
What's going on?

559
01:06:53,050 --> 01:06:54,593
Move it, people.

560
01:06:55,720 --> 01:06:57,430
Please, sir, stand back.

561
01:06:57,763 --> 01:06:59,223
Yes, sir.

562
01:07:00,808 --> 01:07:02,601
Yes, sir.

563
01:07:02,768 --> 01:07:05,271
No, sir. We won't let anything
out to the press.

564
01:07:06,772 --> 01:07:07,940
Yes, sir.

565
01:07:08,983 --> 01:07:12,153
You endangered an entire investigation
by trying to push something.

566
01:07:12,319 --> 01:07:14,155
Not to mention your own lives.

567
01:07:14,321 --> 01:07:16,282
You blew the whole Palancio stakeout.

568
01:07:16,449 --> 01:07:19,326
Instead of keeping him under surveillance
as I told you to...

569
01:07:19,493 --> 01:07:22,872
...you had to harass him.
What do you have to say about that?

570
01:07:23,039 --> 01:07:24,582
What do I tell Avery? What?

571
01:07:27,835 --> 01:07:31,505
You tell him it's not Palancio.
You tell him it's a traffic cop.

572
01:07:33,382 --> 01:07:35,634
- A cop?
- That's right.

573
01:07:35,801 --> 01:07:38,137
A traffic cop. Are you out of your mind?

574
01:07:39,555 --> 01:07:42,475
Do you expect me to believe
that a traffic cop...

575
01:07:42,808 --> 01:07:46,187
...is killing off all the top criminals
in the city? Who?

576
01:07:50,816 --> 01:07:52,318
It's Charlie McCoy.

577
01:07:53,486 --> 01:07:56,697
He's ready for the rubber gun squad.
He even tried to kill himself.

578
01:07:57,281 --> 01:07:59,283
Charlie McCoy.

579
01:08:00,242 --> 01:08:01,952
Harry...

580
01:08:02,661 --> 01:08:04,997
...Guzman was hit today.

581
01:08:06,499 --> 01:08:09,543
A cop was killed. It was Charlie McCoy.

582
01:08:14,173 --> 01:08:16,675
- McCoy?
- Yes, Charlie McCoy.

583
01:08:17,009 --> 01:08:19,845
The only reason I don't bust you
into the bag this minute...

584
01:08:20,012 --> 01:08:23,140
...is I know the two of you
were close friends.

585
01:08:23,307 --> 01:08:26,936
I was just about to call his wife.
Or you can, if you want to.

586
01:08:27,103 --> 01:08:29,313
I know he had kids.

587
01:08:29,480 --> 01:08:31,023
Yeah.

588
01:08:32,399 --> 01:08:34,443
- Who reported it?
- Davis.

589
01:08:34,610 --> 01:08:35,653
Davis?

590
01:08:35,820 --> 01:08:38,531
What happened
to the DiGiorgio stakeout team?

591
01:08:38,697 --> 01:08:42,493
It was an accidental coincidence.
Davis happened to be going by, it happens.

592
01:08:42,660 --> 01:08:44,745
McCoy was already dead
when he got there.

593
01:08:45,621 --> 01:08:48,499
- Any witnesses?
- None.

594
01:08:51,127 --> 01:08:53,129
- I'll make that call.
- Go ahead.

595
01:08:54,046 --> 01:08:57,842
Harry, if it means anything coming
from me, I'm sorry about Charlie.

596
01:08:58,008 --> 01:09:00,219
But it's Palancio, believe me.

597
01:09:00,386 --> 01:09:03,931
I'll have a warrant in 48 hours.
You can pick him up.

598
01:09:04,098 --> 01:09:05,516
He's all yours.

599
01:09:40,926 --> 01:09:43,095
Well, thank you for coming, Harry.

600
01:09:43,971 --> 01:09:45,764
You sure you have to leave?

601
01:09:47,099 --> 01:09:50,311
I won't have any place to go
for a sit-down dinner anymore.

602
01:09:51,645 --> 01:09:54,148
I never really did like it here very much.

603
01:09:55,608 --> 01:09:57,943
I always liked the change of seasons.

604
01:10:03,782 --> 01:10:07,912
I'm gonna take him home. It's time.

605
01:10:08,078 --> 01:10:11,040
It's time he went home.

606
01:10:15,628 --> 01:10:18,631
Come on, kids, let's get in the car.

607
01:10:27,431 --> 01:10:31,852
It was nice of that young man
to help us with the children.

608
01:10:33,854 --> 01:10:37,691
Goodbye, Harry. We'll all miss you.

609
01:10:37,858 --> 01:10:39,360
Bye, doll.

610
01:10:46,242 --> 01:10:48,827
Take them
to the passenger terminal, please.

611
01:10:58,837 --> 01:11:02,049
It was nice of you to come out.
You didn't have to do that.

612
01:11:02,675 --> 01:11:05,344
If I'd have been there sooner,
he might still be alive.

613
01:11:06,845 --> 01:11:09,515
He didn't deserve to get it that way.

614
01:11:10,683 --> 01:11:12,685
If there's anything I can do...

615
01:11:14,019 --> 01:11:16,605
I feel responsible somehow.

616
01:11:45,175 --> 01:11:47,720
The next shooter is Callahan.
Davis on deck.

617
01:12:29,553 --> 01:12:32,806
You sure shot the pants off
of everybody with that score, Harry.

618
01:12:32,973 --> 01:12:34,850
I've never seen you smoother.

619
01:12:35,434 --> 01:12:37,936
By the way,
I personally want to tell you...

620
01:12:38,103 --> 01:12:41,190
...how sorry I am
about what happened to Charlie.

621
01:12:41,982 --> 01:12:46,153
What I can't figure out, Frank,
is how that kid Davis got in there first.

622
01:12:46,320 --> 01:12:48,614
You guys were right across the street.

623
01:12:48,947 --> 01:12:53,619
I don't have a goddamned idea, Harry.
The kid came out of nowhere.

624
01:12:54,495 --> 01:12:57,122
We were in that garage
before you could spit.

625
01:12:57,498 --> 01:13:00,959
Maybe I'm slowing down in my old age
or something, I don't know.

626
01:13:01,627 --> 01:13:05,631
I wanna be the first to congratulate you
on what I think will be the winning score.

627
01:13:05,798 --> 01:13:07,633
You shaded me by seven points.

628
01:13:07,800 --> 01:13:10,886
The only person now
who has a chance is Davis.

629
01:13:16,183 --> 01:13:17,976
Shoot them up.

630
01:13:53,846 --> 01:13:56,181
I think the kid beat you, Harry.

631
01:13:57,724 --> 01:13:59,101
It happens.

632
01:13:59,268 --> 01:14:02,146
Harry, he edged you by four points.

633
01:14:02,312 --> 01:14:04,898
That evens it up on the overall champion.

634
01:14:05,649 --> 01:14:07,651
You have your choice in the shoot-off.

635
01:14:08,068 --> 01:14:10,154
Bull's eye or combat?

636
01:14:13,282 --> 01:14:14,992
Combat.

637
01:14:59,745 --> 01:15:01,371
Out!

638
01:15:09,254 --> 01:15:12,132
Five, 46 seconds. Score, perfect.

639
01:15:13,258 --> 01:15:14,635
Good luck, sir.

640
01:15:54,800 --> 01:15:57,511
A good guy!
That last one was a good guy.

641
01:16:10,774 --> 01:16:13,902
Thirty-six seconds.
But I'm sorry, Harry, you hit a good guy.

642
01:16:14,069 --> 01:16:16,196
You had a bad break.
I really don't deserve it.

643
01:16:16,363 --> 01:16:17,698
Well, you won, didn't you?

644
01:16:17,864 --> 01:16:19,825
- Yes, sir, but-
- That's all that matters.

645
01:16:19,992 --> 01:16:21,493
You mind if I try that one?

646
01:16:27,583 --> 01:16:29,668
Chester, how about six?

647
01:16:48,312 --> 01:16:50,856
Not bad. I seem to have lost the last one.

648
01:16:52,107 --> 01:16:54,026
You get used to it.

649
01:16:56,361 --> 01:16:59,031
I can see how you would, at that.

650
01:17:55,420 --> 01:17:58,423
You said five minutes
and I've been waiting for half an hour.

651
01:17:58,590 --> 01:18:00,717
Don't you ever get hungry?

652
01:18:03,595 --> 01:18:07,599
- It just didn't seem like a half-hour.
- Yeah, well, it has been.

653
01:18:07,766 --> 01:18:10,894
I went over to my butcher's yesterday
and picked up some veal.

654
01:18:11,061 --> 01:18:15,399
Pops is really an artist, man. I could
watch that man cut meat all day long.

655
01:18:16,775 --> 01:18:18,777
Why don't you
come home with me and...

656
01:18:18,944 --> 01:18:21,780
My wife's a good cook.
Have a little dinner with us.

657
01:18:28,120 --> 01:18:31,957
No, thanks. I just saw something
that killed my appetite.

658
01:18:40,298 --> 01:18:44,219
We'll catch those animals with their pants
down. I was going to call you at home.

659
01:18:44,386 --> 01:18:46,847
We got our search warrants
and multiple charges.

660
01:18:47,013 --> 01:18:49,599
We're gonna make a city-wide raid
tomorrow morning.

661
01:18:49,766 --> 01:18:54,020
Palancio is yours.
Just don't take him out head-first, Harry.

662
01:18:54,521 --> 01:18:58,316
I think you'll find what I want to show you
in ballistics very interesting.

663
01:18:58,483 --> 01:19:01,862
You'll find more leads than you can
shake a stick at tomorrow morning.

664
01:19:06,491 --> 01:19:08,535
- Good morning, Harry. Sir.
- Walter.

665
01:19:08,702 --> 01:19:10,871
Do you mind excusing us
for a few minutes?

666
01:19:11,037 --> 01:19:12,581
Sure.

667
01:19:21,465 --> 01:19:22,549
There's only two.

668
01:19:22,716 --> 01:19:26,344
- I wonder what happened to the others.
- Federal boys have them.

669
01:19:48,492 --> 01:19:49,493
Well?

670
01:19:50,368 --> 01:19:52,204
Take a look.

671
01:19:56,708 --> 01:19:58,543
Close, real close.

672
01:19:59,711 --> 01:20:02,714
But there's still a lot of lines
that don't match up.

673
01:20:02,881 --> 01:20:05,091
All this proves is that these two bullets...

674
01:20:05,258 --> 01:20:08,762
...came from barrels
with a similar twist and width of rifling.

675
01:20:08,929 --> 01:20:11,097
You don't think it would stand up
as evidence?

676
01:20:11,264 --> 01:20:12,808
As it is, no.

677
01:20:12,974 --> 01:20:15,769
But I'll have a full comparison report made,
no problem.

678
01:20:15,936 --> 01:20:19,272
You're probably right.
Besides, it isn't necessary yet.

679
01:20:19,439 --> 01:20:21,274
What do you mean, "yet"?

680
01:20:21,441 --> 01:20:23,026
Where'd you get that slug?

681
01:20:23,193 --> 01:20:26,905
- I'd just as soon not say for the time being.
- Don't play games on this.

682
01:20:27,072 --> 01:20:28,532
Whose side are you on anyway?

683
01:20:28,698 --> 01:20:31,535
It's just a wild shot
and I'm probably wrong.

684
01:20:31,701 --> 01:20:34,246
I'd like to handle it my own way.

685
01:20:34,996 --> 01:20:38,667
By the way, I'd like to have Davis
and Sweet as my back-up squad tomorrow.

686
01:20:38,834 --> 01:20:42,003
Davis and Sweet?
They're just rookies, for chrissake.

687
01:20:42,170 --> 01:20:45,549
You drum up somebody in the department
who can shoot as well and I'll use them.

688
01:20:45,715 --> 01:20:48,218
Goddamn it,
there isn't supposed to be any shooting.

689
01:20:49,094 --> 01:20:52,222
Besides, they don't have the experience yet
for a job like this.

690
01:20:52,389 --> 01:20:56,226
How the hell's a man supposed to get
experience if nobody gives him a chance?

691
01:20:56,393 --> 01:20:58,395
And Davis is the new pistol champion.

692
01:20:58,562 --> 01:21:01,189
Suppose they panic and start shooting?

693
01:21:02,983 --> 01:21:07,946
Nothing wrong with shooting,
as long as the right people get shot.

694
01:21:24,296 --> 01:21:27,924
- Let him know who you are and keep cool.
- Okay.

695
01:21:28,091 --> 01:21:30,594
I want you to keep an eye
on Davis and Sweet.

696
01:21:30,760 --> 01:21:31,803
What for?

697
01:21:31,970 --> 01:21:33,847
Just do it, will you?

698
01:21:35,348 --> 01:21:36,641
All right.

699
01:21:36,808 --> 01:21:38,685
- You all set?
- All set.

700
01:21:38,852 --> 01:21:40,478
We'll take off in three cars.

701
01:21:40,645 --> 01:21:43,189
Davis and Sweet will make the arrest.
Early will cover.

702
01:21:43,356 --> 01:21:46,568
I'll be on the back at the pier
in case anybody makes a break for it.

703
01:21:46,735 --> 01:21:49,154
If there'll be trouble,
that's where it'll start.

704
01:21:49,321 --> 01:21:52,449
We're holding the other squads back
until you've made your arrest.

705
01:21:52,616 --> 01:21:56,912
Yours is the most important, it'll be
the first. We don't want any foul-ups.

706
01:21:57,078 --> 01:21:58,663
- Right?
- Right.

707
01:22:00,665 --> 01:22:04,002
I'd never walk up to a door with Harry,
too many people don't like him.

708
01:22:04,544 --> 01:22:07,964
Thanks. I needed that.

709
01:22:10,675 --> 01:22:12,135
- You boys ready?
- Yes, sir.

710
01:22:12,302 --> 01:22:15,430
- Thank you for requesting us.
- Sir, we won't let you down.

711
01:22:15,597 --> 01:22:17,807
Well, I'm depending on that.

712
01:23:24,749 --> 01:23:25,959
Yeah?

713
01:23:29,337 --> 01:23:31,089
Who is this?

714
01:23:37,762 --> 01:23:39,681
What was that, Nickie?

715
01:23:42,434 --> 01:23:46,896
Somebody said we'll be hit in two minutes.
They'll be dressed like cops.

716
01:23:47,772 --> 01:23:50,191
Did it sound like anybody you know?

717
01:23:50,358 --> 01:23:52,777
No, I couldn't tell.

718
01:24:08,001 --> 01:24:09,794
Ed, Chuck...

719
01:24:12,797 --> 01:24:14,507
...get over to the windows.

720
01:24:18,303 --> 01:24:19,512
I got the water side.

721
01:24:19,679 --> 01:24:21,806
I'll take the street side.

722
01:24:21,973 --> 01:24:24,059
If they are cops, this could be a set-up.

723
01:24:24,225 --> 01:24:27,145
After the holes they put in Ricca
you want me to wait and see?

724
01:24:27,312 --> 01:24:29,189
If they're cops, they'll have papers.

725
01:24:29,355 --> 01:24:31,191
Car coming, Frank.

726
01:24:31,357 --> 01:24:33,985
There's a big guy out there.

727
01:24:37,072 --> 01:24:39,991
- He got a uniform on?
- No.

728
01:24:40,950 --> 01:24:44,204
He ain't no cop.
Cops always come in the front door.

729
01:24:44,662 --> 01:24:46,206
Another car.

730
01:24:46,998 --> 01:24:49,417
Why didn't they come in squad cars
if they're cops?

731
01:24:49,584 --> 01:24:53,421
That big guy's working himself around
by those containers.

732
01:24:54,339 --> 01:24:56,466
He's got a gun out.

733
01:24:56,633 --> 01:24:58,009
Two uniforms in it.

734
01:24:59,344 --> 01:25:01,679
That ain't no cop's gun, Frank.

735
01:25:06,601 --> 01:25:09,979
There's a cop in uniform coming up
to the door.

736
01:25:15,360 --> 01:25:18,446
We ain't open. Come back tomorrow.

737
01:25:18,613 --> 01:25:21,199
Police officers,
we'd like to ask you some questions.

738
01:25:21,366 --> 01:25:24,035
I'm just a watchman. Nobody's here.

739
01:25:24,202 --> 01:25:25,995
We're looking for Mr. Frank Palancio.

740
01:25:26,162 --> 01:25:28,832
Would you open the door?
We have a warrant for his arrest.

741
01:25:28,998 --> 01:25:30,542
I said nobody's here, goddamn it!

742
01:25:30,708 --> 01:25:33,044
We have warrants
for a search of the premises.

743
01:25:33,211 --> 01:25:34,921
Serve them!

744
01:25:49,561 --> 01:25:52,063
They got Sweet! Send some help, quick!

745
01:26:39,736 --> 01:26:40,987
Cease firing.

746
01:26:41,154 --> 01:26:44,616
Throw your weapons out and come out
with your hands behind your heads.

747
01:26:44,782 --> 01:26:46,868
- Bullshit!
- Fuck you!

748
01:28:46,029 --> 01:28:50,074
You sure you don't want a local for this?
Takes about seven stitches.

749
01:28:50,241 --> 01:28:51,784
No, thanks.

750
01:28:53,077 --> 01:28:55,413
Okay, it's your ass.

751
01:28:55,955 --> 01:28:58,666
My head, cut's on my head.

752
01:28:59,834 --> 01:29:02,920
Why does everybody suddenly
become a comedian in here?

753
01:29:03,171 --> 01:29:05,089
Does he have to stay in here?

754
01:29:05,923 --> 01:29:10,428
No, I could stop and let the man's
brains run out all over his shoes.

755
01:29:10,595 --> 01:29:13,973
Rogers, I don't need to have a doctor
display that kind of attitude.

756
01:29:14,140 --> 01:29:15,933
A police officer is dead.

757
01:29:16,851 --> 01:29:18,353
Sorry.

758
01:29:19,604 --> 01:29:22,565
I got those warrants
for a search of the premises, Callahan...

759
01:29:22,732 --> 01:29:25,610
...not for you to become
judge, jury and executioner.

760
01:29:25,777 --> 01:29:28,404
It was supposed to be a simple arrest.

761
01:29:29,113 --> 01:29:32,617
Arresting a killer like Palancio
isn't always simple.

762
01:29:32,784 --> 01:29:35,745
People are guilty until proven-
I mean...

763
01:29:36,704 --> 01:29:38,790
Goddamn it, you know what I mean.

764
01:29:38,956 --> 01:29:41,959
The city's on the edge
of the worst violence in its history...

765
01:29:42,126 --> 01:29:44,921
...and you have to start
full-scale military operations.

766
01:29:45,088 --> 01:29:48,466
I didn't start shooting at anyone
who didn't start shooting at me first.

767
01:29:48,633 --> 01:29:52,970
Each time you pull out that gun,
my paperwork backs up for three months.

768
01:29:53,137 --> 01:29:55,807
The chief and I have already
conferred on this matter.

769
01:29:55,973 --> 01:29:58,184
A full investigation is warranted here.

770
01:30:03,314 --> 01:30:05,483
What about a dead cop?

771
01:30:06,234 --> 01:30:09,654
- I warned you against taking them.
- Sweet was killed with the first shot.

772
01:30:09,821 --> 01:30:14,450
Besides, they were tipped off.
They knew we were coming, Briggs.

773
01:30:14,617 --> 01:30:17,453
How? Don't hand me that crap.

774
01:30:17,620 --> 01:30:20,832
They knew we were coming.
After 200 arrests, I know the difference.

775
01:30:22,500 --> 01:30:26,504
If I have my way, Callahan, you won't make
another arrest as long as you live.

776
01:30:28,840 --> 01:30:30,216
Is that all, lieutenant?

777
01:30:31,175 --> 01:30:33,636
No, that's not all.

778
01:30:34,554 --> 01:30:36,305
I want that slug you showed me.

779
01:30:38,391 --> 01:30:42,228
I ran that through ballistics, it was
nothing. The rifling was totally different.

780
01:30:42,395 --> 01:30:45,022
It's still state's evidence.
I want it anyway.

781
01:30:50,153 --> 01:30:51,737
Eat it.

782
01:31:13,176 --> 01:31:18,181
Look, Harry, if it means anything,
I think you got the wrong end of the stick.

783
01:31:18,347 --> 01:31:20,057
- You do?
- Yeah.

784
01:31:20,224 --> 01:31:22,393
What did they find
when they got in there?

785
01:31:22,560 --> 01:31:25,980
Nothing. Palancio was as clean
as he could possibly be.

786
01:31:26,731 --> 01:31:28,774
They knew we were coming, Harry.

787
01:31:29,066 --> 01:31:31,277
Why do you figure they opened up on us?

788
01:31:31,736 --> 01:31:34,697
They must've thought
it was a set-up like the others.

789
01:31:35,072 --> 01:31:37,074
- It was.
- No.

790
01:31:38,409 --> 01:31:40,077
It was a set-up, Early.

791
01:31:41,913 --> 01:31:46,375
What I'm gonna lay on you seems so
far-fetched, I can't even believe it myself.

792
01:31:47,084 --> 01:31:50,338
I gave up being surprised
working with you anyway.

793
01:31:51,255 --> 01:31:53,466
Would you be surprised if I told you...

794
01:31:53,633 --> 01:31:57,595
...a bunch of rookie cops were the ones
who were doing all the killing?

795
01:31:59,096 --> 01:32:00,223
See this?

796
01:32:00,389 --> 01:32:03,309
I gave Briggs a phony for the time being.

797
01:32:03,476 --> 01:32:05,811
This is a bullet I took out
of the target range.

798
01:32:05,978 --> 01:32:07,939
It came from Davis' gun.

799
01:32:08,105 --> 01:32:11,442
It matches up with the one
taken out of Charlie McCoy's body.

800
01:32:11,984 --> 01:32:14,195
Davis? That's insane.

801
01:32:14,362 --> 01:32:17,823
Maybe so, but somebody tipped-off
Palancio that we were coming.

802
01:32:18,032 --> 01:32:22,245
Wanting me killed or Palancio
or hopefully both.

803
01:32:22,411 --> 01:32:25,957
Yeah, but Sweet died today.

804
01:32:26,123 --> 01:32:28,709
Sweet was sacrificed.

805
01:32:29,544 --> 01:32:32,505
What's more important, if I'm right,
I'll be sacrificed.

806
01:32:32,672 --> 01:32:36,259
They've gotta figure I told you,
which means you'll be sacrificed.

807
01:32:38,970 --> 01:32:40,137
Yeah.

808
01:32:41,556 --> 01:32:45,643
If anything happens to me,
I want you to give that to Lt. Briggs.

809
01:32:45,810 --> 01:32:48,771
Okay. What happens
if they get us both?

810
01:32:49,397 --> 01:32:51,315
Then they win.

811
01:32:53,359 --> 01:32:57,196
It's not hard to understand
how this could happen, the way things are.

812
01:32:57,363 --> 01:33:01,284
As incredible as it seems, there may be
a sub-organization within the police force.

813
01:33:01,450 --> 01:33:05,162
Sort of a death squad
like they had in Brazil some years back.

814
01:33:06,372 --> 01:33:07,957
Damn.

815
01:33:09,166 --> 01:33:14,338
Some nights I wake up, wonder
where the hell the world's going to.

816
01:33:16,841 --> 01:33:20,469
I want you to take care of yourself,
you understand?

817
01:33:52,084 --> 01:33:54,795
- Hi.
- Hi.

818
01:33:54,962 --> 01:33:57,548
Jesus, what happened to your face?

819
01:33:57,715 --> 01:33:59,592
Nothing, just a few stitches.

820
01:34:01,552 --> 01:34:05,389
I was going to the market,
how about if I bring back a few beers?

821
01:34:05,556 --> 01:34:07,850
Good, I could use a beer right about now.

822
01:34:08,017 --> 01:34:10,227
I've got your key,
so I'll get your mail too.

823
01:34:10,394 --> 01:34:11,771
All right, baby.

824
01:34:12,271 --> 01:34:14,065
Keep it warm.

825
01:34:38,756 --> 01:34:42,551
Do you have any idea how hard it is
to prosecute a cop?

826
01:35:00,069 --> 01:35:03,280
You heroes have killed
a dozen people this week.

827
01:35:04,490 --> 01:35:06,826
What are you gonna do next week?

828
01:35:09,328 --> 01:35:10,913
Kill a dozen more.

829
01:35:12,289 --> 01:35:14,959
Is that what you guys are all about,
being heroes?

830
01:35:15,126 --> 01:35:17,086
All our heroes are dead.

831
01:35:17,253 --> 01:35:18,921
We are the first generation...

832
01:35:19,213 --> 01:35:21,549
...that's learned to fight.

833
01:35:21,716 --> 01:35:24,885
We're simply ridding society
of killers that would be caught...

834
01:35:25,052 --> 01:35:27,930
...and sentenced anyway
if our courts worked properly.

835
01:35:29,557 --> 01:35:33,811
We began with the criminals
that the people know...

836
01:35:34,645 --> 01:35:37,314
...so that our actions
would be understood.

837
01:35:38,524 --> 01:35:42,236
It's not just a question
of whether or not to use violence.

838
01:35:43,988 --> 01:35:46,323
There simply is no other way, inspector.

839
01:35:47,742 --> 01:35:49,744
You of all people...

840
01:35:49,910 --> 01:35:52,163
...should understand that.

841
01:35:54,999 --> 01:35:57,835
Either you're for us or you're against us.

842
01:36:04,008 --> 01:36:06,385
I'm afraid you've misjudged me.

843
01:38:09,174 --> 01:38:11,594
- Hi, Sunny.
- Hi, Sue.

844
01:38:17,975 --> 01:38:19,101
No, no!

845
01:38:20,477 --> 01:38:23,397
Harry, what are you doing?

846
01:38:29,820 --> 01:38:31,947
Hey, what's going on down here?

847
01:38:32,114 --> 01:38:34,700
I'm taking the mailbox apart,
what does it look like?

848
01:38:34,867 --> 01:38:37,202
- You people live here, don't you?
- Yeah.

849
01:38:38,120 --> 01:38:41,040
What are you doing to the mailbox?
Did you lose you key?

850
01:38:41,206 --> 01:38:44,251
Why don't you mind
your own goddamn business?

851
01:38:44,418 --> 01:38:47,671
That's my mailbox too.
Don't you get smart with me.

852
01:38:49,006 --> 01:38:51,175
Tampering with the mail
is a federal offense.

853
01:38:51,342 --> 01:38:53,177
I'm calling the police.

854
01:38:54,136 --> 01:38:55,346
I am the police.

855
01:38:56,764 --> 01:38:57,848
What?

856
01:39:00,184 --> 01:39:01,685
The cop that lives upstairs?

857
01:39:20,371 --> 01:39:21,872
What's that?

858
01:39:23,666 --> 01:39:25,084
Plastic explosive.

859
01:39:27,086 --> 01:39:28,212
A bomb?

860
01:39:28,712 --> 01:39:29,880
That's right.

861
01:39:30,047 --> 01:39:33,092
If you'd bothered me any more,
we'd all be stuck to the ceiling.

862
01:39:33,258 --> 01:39:36,887
- Do you want to hold it?
- No. I don't want to get involved.

863
01:39:39,390 --> 01:39:42,351
Go to your apartment and stay there.
Don't open for anybody.

864
01:41:01,138 --> 01:41:02,973
Damn it.

865
01:41:12,524 --> 01:41:13,734
Operator.

866
01:41:13,901 --> 01:41:17,321
Homicide, Lt. Briggs,
Inspector Callahan calling.

867
01:41:20,199 --> 01:41:22,409
Callahan, where are you?

868
01:41:22,576 --> 01:41:24,870
Look, Briggs,
I just found a bomb in my mailbox.

869
01:41:25,037 --> 01:41:27,956
I want you to get a man
over to Early's house right away.

870
01:41:28,123 --> 01:41:31,168
- What?
- I've got a bomb right here.

871
01:41:31,335 --> 01:41:33,337
Now get a man over to Early's,
you hear me?

872
01:41:34,046 --> 01:41:35,672
Right.

873
01:41:35,839 --> 01:41:38,467
Stay right where you are.
I'll be down there myself.

874
01:41:38,634 --> 01:41:40,260
Don't move.

875
01:42:22,719 --> 01:42:24,221
Yeah?

876
01:42:33,230 --> 01:42:34,565
Come on in.

877
01:42:37,025 --> 01:42:39,736
I don't like looking down one of those.

878
01:42:42,489 --> 01:42:44,074
Where's the bomb?

879
01:42:44,992 --> 01:42:46,577
Right on the dresser.

880
01:42:49,246 --> 01:42:52,916
All right. Let's get out of here.

881
01:42:53,917 --> 01:42:55,669
Avery will want to see this.

882
01:43:06,388 --> 01:43:10,142
You mind driving?
I want to take a closer look at this thing.

883
01:43:31,955 --> 01:43:34,791
This thing could be activated
by your mailbox key.

884
01:43:36,126 --> 01:43:37,920
Or by a timer.

885
01:43:41,131 --> 01:43:42,966
Turn right, here.

886
01:43:47,304 --> 01:43:49,514
Get on the freeway.

887
01:43:49,681 --> 01:43:51,600
The freeway?

888
01:43:52,309 --> 01:43:55,020
You got a new route to city hall,
lieutenant?

889
01:44:02,653 --> 01:44:06,448
Your gun's out of its holster, Briggs.
First time?

890
01:44:06,615 --> 01:44:08,617
You know you're not going to city hall.

891
01:44:08,784 --> 01:44:11,828
The only way you're going anywhere
is in a rubber bag.

892
01:44:12,537 --> 01:44:14,331
Let me have your gun.

893
01:44:33,725 --> 01:44:35,018
Now the shells.

894
01:44:39,356 --> 01:44:42,025
Three. You always carry three.

895
01:44:47,364 --> 01:44:49,074
Throw them out the window.

896
01:44:55,372 --> 01:44:57,749
How do you figure on pulling this off,
Briggs?

897
01:44:57,916 --> 01:45:01,586
I run the investigation. With your record,
I can make anything stick.

898
01:45:02,879 --> 01:45:05,507
What I can't understand is,
why you of all people?

899
01:45:05,674 --> 01:45:08,593
A hundred years ago in this city,
people did the same thing.

900
01:45:08,760 --> 01:45:11,722
History justified the vigilantes,
we're no different.

901
01:45:12,097 --> 01:45:15,726
Anyone who threatens the security
of the people will be executed.

902
01:45:16,226 --> 01:45:21,064
- Evil for evil, Harry. Retribution.
- That's just fine.

903
01:45:21,231 --> 01:45:23,650
But how does murder fit in?

904
01:45:23,817 --> 01:45:26,445
When police start becoming
their own executioners...

905
01:45:26,611 --> 01:45:29,114
...where's it gonna end, Briggs?

906
01:45:29,281 --> 01:45:32,284
Pretty soon, you'll start executing people
for jaywalking.

907
01:45:32,451 --> 01:45:35,245
And executing people for traffic violations.

908
01:45:35,412 --> 01:45:39,416
Then you end up executing your neighbor
because his dog pisses on your lawn.

909
01:45:40,083 --> 01:45:43,628
There isn't one man we've killed that
didn't deserve what was coming to him.

910
01:45:43,795 --> 01:45:46,548
Yes, there is. Charlie McCoy.

911
01:45:46,715 --> 01:45:49,593
- What would you have done?
- I'd have upheld the law.

912
01:45:49,760 --> 01:45:51,970
What the hell do you know
about the law?

913
01:45:52,137 --> 01:45:53,930
You're a great cop, Harry.

914
01:45:54,097 --> 01:45:57,642
You had a chance to join the team,
but you'd rather stick to the system.

915
01:45:57,809 --> 01:46:01,146
Briggs, I hate the goddamn system.
But until someone comes along...

916
01:46:01,313 --> 01:46:04,441
...with some changes that make sense,
I'll stick with it.

917
01:46:04,608 --> 01:46:07,319
You're about to become extinct.

918
01:46:11,448 --> 01:46:13,116
Get off at the next exit.

919
01:55:18,161 --> 01:55:19,787
Red?

920
01:55:49,859 --> 01:55:51,569
Red?

921
01:58:10,416 --> 01:58:14,295
Briggs was right.
You guys don't have enough experience.

922
01:58:55,044 --> 01:58:57,505
Just hold it right there, Callahan.

923
01:58:59,048 --> 01:59:00,216
No tricks.

924
01:59:12,061 --> 01:59:14,105
Your organization's through, Briggs.

925
01:59:15,565 --> 01:59:18,359
There's a lot more where they came from,
believe me.

926
01:59:18,526 --> 01:59:21,904
Move out of the way. Move it!

927
01:59:49,765 --> 01:59:51,100
Uphold the law.

928
01:59:53,769 --> 01:59:57,106
You just killed three
police officers, Harry.

929
02:00:01,152 --> 02:00:04,071
And the only reason
I'm not gonna kill you...

930
02:00:04,238 --> 02:00:07,325
...is because I'm gonna prosecute you
with your own system.

931
02:00:15,625 --> 02:00:18,336
It'll be my word against yours.

932
02:00:19,170 --> 02:00:21,214
And who's gonna believe you?

933
02:00:21,964 --> 02:00:25,426
You're a killer, Harry. A maniac.

934
02:01:21,983 --> 02:01:25,152
A man's got to know his limitations.


